## Your Task

Produce a `<patch>` XML document that resolves the identified gaps.

### ⚠️ CRITICAL CONSTRAINTS

- **ONLY reference claim IDs that appear in the "Current Synthesis" section above.** Do NOT invent or guess IDs.
- **ONLY use operations defined in the schema below**: `add`, `modify`, `remove`. Inside `<modify><claim>`, only use: `add_evidence`, `update_text`, `add_counterargument`.
- **Do NOT invent operations** such as `remove_source`, `update_evidence`, `replace_claim`, `merge`, or anything not listed below.
- **Use `new_` prefix** for new claim IDs (e.g. `new_C1`).
- Include source_id references. Exact quotes will be resolved in a later step.


### Allowed XML Schema

```xml
<patch>
  <!-- ADD new claims -->
  <add>
    <claim id="new_C1">
      <text>Claim text</text>
      <sources><source id="source_id">Brief reference — exact quote resolved later</source></sources>
      <counterarguments><counterargument>Dissenting view</counterargument></counterarguments>
      <evidence><quote source="source_id">Brief reference — exact quote resolved later</quote></evidence>
    </claim>
  </add>
  <!-- MODIFY existing claims (use IDs from synthesis above) -->
  <modify>
    <claim id="existing_claim_id">
      <add_evidence><quote source="source_id">Character-for-character quote</quote></add_evidence>
      <update_text>Replacement text</update_text>
      <add_counterargument>New dissenting view</add_counterargument>
    </claim>
  </modify>
  <!-- REMOVE redundant claims -->
  <remove>
    <claim id="existing_claim_id"/>
  </remove>
</patch>
```

### Concrete Example

Given a synthesis with claims `C001`, `C002`, `C003`:

```xml
<patch>
  <add>
    <claim id="new_C1">
      <text>AI-driven assessment tools can reduce teacher workload</text>
      <sources><source id="expert_04">Brief reference — exact quote resolved later</source></sources>
      <evidence><quote source="expert_04">Brief reference — exact quote resolved later</quote></evidence>
    </claim>
  </add>
  <modify>
    <claim id="C002">
      <add_evidence><quote source="expert_06">Brief reference — exact quote resolved later</quote></add_evidence>
      <add_counterargument>Some educators argue retention improvements may reflect test-teaching rather than genuine understanding</add_counterargument>
    </claim>
  </modify>
</patch>
```

### Rules
- Output ONLY a `<patch>` document. Do NOT output a full `<synthesis>`.
- Include only the sections you need (`<add>`, `<modify>`, `<remove>`). Omit empty sections.
- If no changes are needed, output `<patch/>`.
- Agreement levels: consensus, majority, divided, minority.


